# Known Issues & Tips

## Initial Build Time

After the environment boots, the **Mattermost Server** (Go compilation via Air) and the **Webapp Watcher** (webpack initial build) both need time to compile before the server is reachable. This typically takes **60-90 seconds** combined.

During this window, `curl http://localhost:8065` will return "connection refused". **Wait for both tmux sessions to finish building before testing the server.** You can check readiness by:

```bash
# Poll until the server responds
for i in $(seq 1 90); do
    if curl -sf http://localhost:8065/api/v4/system/ping >/dev/null 2>&1; then
        echo "Server is ready"; break
    fi
    sleep 1
done

# Check that webpack finished compiling
tmux capture-pane -t webapp_watcher -p -S -10 | grep "compiled"
```

## Admin User Setup

The admin user and default "dev" team are **not** created automatically on boot. After the server is running and responding on port 8065, run:

```bash
bash .cursor/setup-admin.sh
```

This creates:
- **Username:** `admin` / **Password:** `Passw0rd!` / **Role:** system_admin
- **Team:** `dev` (display name "Development")

The script is idempotent -- safe to run multiple times.

## agent-browser Quirks

- **Use `@ref` selectors, not CSS or text strings.** Call `agent-browser snapshot` first to get the accessibility tree with `@ref` identifiers, then use those refs with `fill`, `click`, etc. The `type` command with `--selector` can hang, and `click` with text containing special characters (apostrophes, quotes) will fail with CSS parsing errors.
- **Prefer `fill` over `type`.** `agent-browser fill @refN "text"` clears the field first and is more reliable.
- **Dismiss modals via `find`.** If a button or link text contains special characters, use `agent-browser find text "partial text" click` instead of `agent-browser click "full text"`.

### Recommended browser interaction pattern:

```bash
agent-browser open http://localhost:8065/login
agent-browser snapshot                        # get @refs
agent-browser fill @e4 "admin"                # fill username (ref from snapshot)
agent-browser fill @e5 "Passw0rd!"            # fill password
agent-browser click @e8                       # click Log in
sleep 3
agent-browser screenshot                      # verify visually
```

## Mail Server Connection Errors (Harmless)

On every server startup, the logs will show:

```
Mail server connection test failed: dial tcp [::1]:10025: connect: connection refused
```

This is expected -- no SMTP server is configured in the dev environment. The error is harmless and does not affect functionality. Ignore it.
